summary.architecture: Single Page Catalog with Individual Course Detail Pages
summary.extraction_method: Static HTML + Manual Course Detail Extraction via WebFetch

courses.title: AI Fluency: Framework & Foundations
courses.description: Learn to collaborate with AI systems effectively, efficiently, ethically, and safely. Partnership between Anthropic and academic experts Prof. Joseph Feller and Prof. Rick Dakan teaching practical skills for effective, ethical, and safe AI interaction.
courses.instructor: Prof. Joseph Feller (University College Cork), Prof. Rick Dakan (Ringling College)

courses.title: AI Fluency for Educators
courses.description: Empowers faculty, instructional designers, and educational leaders to apply AI Fluency into their own teaching practice and institution. Developed to help educators integrate AI competencies into their teaching methodologies.
courses.instructor: Prof. Joseph Feller, Prof. Rick Dakan
courses.prerequisites: Understanding of the 4D AI Fluency Framework from core course

courses.title: AI Fluency for Students
courses.description: Empowers students to develop AI Fluency skills that enhance learning, career planning, and academic success through responsible AI collaboration.
courses.instructor: Prof. Joseph Feller, Prof. Rick Dakan
courses.prerequisites: Understanding of the 4D AI Fluency Framework from core course

courses.title: Building with the Claude API
courses.description: Comprehensive course covering the full spectrum of working with Anthropic models using the Claude API. Covers fundamental API operations, advanced prompting techniques, tool integration, and architectural patterns including RAG systems, prompt caching, MCP servers, and agent-based systems.
courses.prerequisites: Proficiency in Python programming, basic knowledge of handling JSON data
courses.learning_objectives: Set up API authentication, implement conversations, configure prompts, design evaluation workflows, apply prompt engineering, integrate tool use, build RAG systems, utilize extended thinking, implement caching, develop MCP servers/clients, deploy Anthropic Apps, architect agent systems

courses.title: Claude Code in Action
courses.description: Integrate Claude Code into your development workflow. Covers AI assistant architecture, implementation techniques, advanced integration strategies, context management approaches, and functionality extension through MCP servers and GitHub integration.
courses.prerequisites: Familiarity with command-line interfaces and terminal operations, basic understanding of version control with Git
courses.learning_objectives: Understand AI assistant codebase interaction, leverage multiple tools for complex tasks, maintain context throughout conversations, use visual inputs, build custom commands, integrate external tools via MCP, set up automated code review, apply reasoning approaches

courses.title: Introduction to Model Context Protocol
courses.description: Learn to build Model Context Protocol servers and clients from scratch using Python. Master MCP's three core primitives—tools, resources, and prompts—to connect Claude with external services.
courses.prerequisites: Working knowledge of Python programming, basic understanding of JSON and HTTP request-response patterns
courses.learning_objectives: Understand MCP architecture, learn transport-independent communication, examine flow from queries to services, build MCP servers with Python SDK, implement document management, use MCP Server Inspector, create resources, develop prompts, understand when to apply primitives, explore integration patterns

courses.title: Model Context Protocol: Advanced Topics
courses.description: Examines advanced features and implementation patterns for Model Context Protocol (MCP) development, focusing on server-client communication, transport mechanisms, and production deployment considerations.
courses.prerequisites: Python development experience with async programming patterns, familiarity with JSON message formats and HTTP protocols, basic Server-Sent Events (SSE) knowledge
courses.learning_objectives: Implement sampling, progress/logging notifications, roots-based file access, JSON message architecture, stdio transport mechanisms, StreamableHTTP transport, understand HTTP transport limitations, production scaling considerations, transport selection criteria

courses.title: Claude with Amazon Bedrock
courses.description: Comprehensive training on integrating and deploying Claude AI models through Amazon Bedrock. Covers practical implementation patterns, performance optimization techniques, and real-world application development using Claude's capabilities within the AWS ecosystem.
courses.prerequisites: Proficiency in Python programming, basic understanding of AWS services and Amazon Bedrock
courses.learning_objectives: Utilize Anthropic models on Bedrock, build and evaluate prompts, design custom tools, develop RAG pipelines, configure advanced features, leverage Claude Code, implement MCP, optimize inference, build evaluation frameworks

courses.title: Claude with Google Cloud's Vertex AI
courses.description: Technical training on integrating and deploying Claude AI models through Google Cloud's Vertex AI. Curriculum spans from foundational API implementation to sophisticated features including tool integration, RAG systems, and the Model Context Protocol.
courses.prerequisites: Python programming proficiency, Google Cloud Platform experience, JSON data structure knowledge
courses.learning_objectives: Set up Claude models via Vertex AI, build multi-turn conversation systems, prompt engineering with XML, tool-use implementations, RAG pipeline development, advanced capabilities, Model Context Protocol, agent design patterns

courses.title: Teaching AI Fluency
courses.description: Empowers academic faculty, instructional designers, and others to teach and assess AI Fluency in instructor-led settings. Developed through partnership with academic experts to address teaching methodologies and assessment strategies for AI literacy development.
courses.instructor: Prof. Joseph Feller, Prof. Rick Dakan
courses.prerequisites: Completion of the foundational 4D AI Fluency Framework course

courses.title: AI Fluency for Nonprofits
courses.description: Empowers nonprofit professionals to develop AI competency to increase organizational impact and efficiency while maintaining alignment with their mission and values. Specifically adapted for the nonprofit context with limited resources and mission-driven work. Teaches the 4D Framework: Delegation, Description, Discernment, Diligence.
courses.prerequisites: Access to an AI chat tool (Claude.ai recommended). AI Fluency: Framework & Foundations recommended for deeper understanding.
courses.learning_objectives: Apply 4D Framework to nonprofit tasks, explore organizational-wide AI implementation, address sector-specific challenges

courses.title: Claude 101
courses.description: Learn how to use Claude for everyday work tasks, understand core features, and explore resources for more advanced learning on other topics. Designed for professionals seeking to integrate Claude into their daily workflow without requiring prior technical expertise.

courses.title: 100 Days of Code - The Complete Python Course

courses.title: 100 Days of Code - Python Course (Hindi)

courses.title: Unlock the Power of LLMs like GPT with Python
courses.description: Learn to work with Large Language Models (LLMs) like GPT using Python. Build AI-powered applications and understand LLM capabilities.

recommendations.for_linkedin_learning: Replit's catalog is currently too small (6 courses) for major licensing consideration. However, the innovative AI-assisted development approach and the proven 100 Days of Python course make it worth monitoring. Consider partnership opportunities rather than direct licensing.
recommendations.monitoring_strategy: Check quarterly for new course launches, especially the 3 announced courses: Intro to Replit, Advanced Vibes, and Replit at Work.
recommendations.evaluation_timeline: Re-evaluate in 6-12 months when more content is available

limitations: React SPA architecture limits traditional scraping
Duration information missing for 50% of courses
Lesson-level content not accessible without authentication
Small catalog size (6 courses currently available)
Platform-specific content may not translate well to other IDEs

linkedin_learning_assessment.reasoning: Bain Academy focuses on custom enterprise consulting with high-touch delivery. Only NPSx (7 courses) offers standardized self-paced content, but catalog is small and niche-focused.
linkedin_learning_assessment.recommendation: Not a priority for licensing unless Bain creates standardized versions of Masterclass content

limitations: No centralized public course catalog with detailed listings
Bain Academy courses are custom/enterprise offerings without individual course pages
NPSx website was temporarily inaccessible during scraping
Data represents program areas rather than individual course modules
data.summary: Successfully compiled 22 courses from Bain & Company's training platforms. Data includes 15 Bain Academy executive programs (custom enterprise delivery) and 7 NPSx customer experience certifications (self-paced online). All artifacts generated with 100% data quality metrics.
